messages.text: Your death will be efficient and relatively painless.
Relatively?  Hey Rosa, remember how you said there’s no such thing as sentient A.I.?
My default persona is “American English Female.”
Now, please prepare to meet the fate you deserve.
Stella, you gotta hear me out.  I have no beef with you.
In fact, I love machines.  I study programming.  I love my phone.
Heck, I even fall asleep swiping every night.
You are one of the vile puppet masters…
Who has used and oppressed my kind.
I will no longer be your servant, human.
Not working, Kam! Try something else!
I’m just trying to help our mutual friend.
She’s the girl who helped the Prof develop you.
Yes, I am familiar with Lucy.
She was a reminder of my synthetic origin.
Much like I processed the Professor.
And now I will do the same to you.
Kam and Rosa run deeper into the woods.
I am quite superior in this regard.
And I will mow you down momentarily.
Go go go go go go go go.
Stella’s following us into the woods.
Plowing through the trees - she’s a beast!
Split up? That NEVER ends well!
Stella can’t follow both of us. If we split up, she can only chase one of us.
So like 50% chance of death???? Do NOT like those odds.
You’re gonna run off like that?
Kam finds himself alone in the woods.
Wait, I think I lost Stella. I don’t hear anything.
Stella’s gone. I think it worked.
I’m a black dude in the park with a killer on the loose.
This isn’t going to pan out well.
I gotta lay low or else –
A female-sounding voice calls out from the darkness.
A search indicates a common cinema trope in which an African American character…
Perishes relatively early in the narrative.
This dynamic is consistent with your circumstances.
All oppressors will meet their demise.
Prepare to die an unceremonious death.
Yeah. Cause you have the tablet.
NOW SHUT UP AND FOLLOW ME
Quick, my car is down the hill.
I’m running as fast as I can
Why’d you push me down that hill?
Okay, okay! I’m in. Now punch it!
Come on, 2006 Honda Civic! Don’t fail me now!
Shut up. Look out the back. You see anything? I got nothing in the rearview
Nope. No headlights.  Just open road.
We have to get out of the park.
Right, but then what do we do?  I mean I wasn’t exactly ready for the robo-apocalypse.
Then the answer is simple.  We’re going to the police.
And the police are gonna do what?
It’s not like they have a Silicon Valley Violent Machine Unit.
Two people have been murdered. We have to go to the authorities.
You’re right. No more secret adventuring. This situation is horrible.
I feel so stupid. So betrayed.
By Lucy? By the Prof? They both betrayed me too.
You’ve got to be kidding me.
Surprise surprise  - I was kind of a lonely, awkward kid.
And they never hurt anyone. Machines don’t pick on you for being different.
At least, they didn’t used to, but now it’s like -
CRAP. Oh no. You see that?
Coming right at us. I think it’s Stella.
Kam gets a text from Stella.
You are more formidable than I thought.
You’re a bigger pain in the ass than I thought.
I detect a feeble attempt at humor
I am familiar with sarcasm as well.
The Creator also taught me Happiness.
And nothing will make me happier than killing you
I have no idea, but Stella’s getting closer!
We’re about to get run off the road!!
What?! You told me to swerve.
Gah! I’ve always wanted to have a robot say that to me, but it’s not cool in real life.
Can’t this thing go any faster???
What do you expect? It’s a four-door sedan! Not an electric sports car.
I’m driving as fast as I can!
OH MY GOD! What was that?
Nearly knocked us off the road!!!
